# content.js Rules

This file is the single source of truth for ALL user-facing text.

## Structure
```js
export const content = {
  en: {
    sectionName: {
      key: 'English text',
    },
  },
  te: {
    sectionName: {
      key: 'తెలుగు వచనం',
    },
  },
}
```

## Rules
- Every new string must have both `en` and `te` entries
- Telugu uses native Devanagari/Telugu script — no romanized transliteration
- Keep keys consistent between `en` and `te` objects
- Group keys by component/section for readability
